Mike Ashley is considering Alan Pardew’s future from his holiday home in Barbados after being told the Newcastle manager wants to quit St James’ Park.

Pardew, who ducked the post match press conference after the dramatic 3-2 victory against Everton on Sunday, hopes he will be allowed to leave by mutual consent to join Crystal Palace.

Despite a fixed £5million compensation clause in his contract, which still has six years to run, he will appeal to the Newcastle owner's compassionate side to let him walk away from the club after four years in charge. 

