Newcastle are ninth in the Barclays Premier League following the victory over Everton and Ashley is happy with the team’s progress following their poor start to the season.

Pardew, who wants to progress and challenge for honours, expected Ashley to make funds available to strengthen the team.

Instead the Newcastle owner, who has an excellent relationship with his manager, appears content with the current squad.

Pardew, who joined Palace in the Eighties and went on to score the winner in the FA Cup semi-final against Liverpool in 1990, is currently at his family home in Surrey waiting for Ashley to make his move. 

