Pardew chose not to speak to the press following Sunday’s 3-2 win over Everton and he would have been aware that such a stance would fuel speculation linking him with a return to south east London.

He returned south on Sunday night after Newcastle’s 3-2 victory over Everton, but is expected to be at the training ground on Tuesday morning as things stand. 

His first team players were given the day off after a hectic Christmas schedule, but the rest of the squad - including non-playing substitutes - reported for work.

Pardew's press conference previewing the New Year's Day visit of Burnley - scheduled for Tuesday - is still planned to go ahead. 

